        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold mb-3">The Ultimate llms.txt Guide</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-400">Published July 21, 2026 · 18 min read · Updated for 2026</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card p-8 mb-6">
        <p class="text-gray-300 text-lg mb-4">
          <strong class="text-white">llms.txt</strong> is the fastest-growing standard in web publishing. In 2026, it's no longer "nice to have" — sites without one are systematically losing citations to competitors that have one.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">
          This is the most complete guide on the web. It covers the official spec, real-world examples from sites that get cited by ChatGPT and Perplexity, the most common mistakes, and a step-by-step workflow you can finish in under an hour.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-400">
          If you're a developer, technical SEO, or running a content site — bookmark this. You'll come back to it.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- TABLE OF CONTENTS -->
      <div class="card p-6 mb-6 bg-geo-500/5 border-geo-500/20">
